Open Omniscience ChangeLog
==========================

This file documents the major changes between versions of Open Omniscience.

---

Version 0.02 (2024-12-19)
------------------------

**MAJOR FEATURE: Local LLM Support**

This release introduces comprehensive local LLM (Large Language Model) support,
enabling advanced text processing capabilities while maintaining full data privacy.

### New Features

#### LLM Core Capabilities
- **Text Generation**: Generate text from prompts with configurable parameters
- **Chat Completion**: Multi-turn conversations with context memory
- **Text Extraction**: Extract structured information including:
  - General text cleaning
  - Named entities (people, organizations, locations, dates)
  - Keywords and key phrases
  - Summaries
  - Metadata (author, date, title, source)
  - Direct quotes with speakers
  - URLs and links
- **Translation**: Translate text between 11+ languages (en, fr, es, de, it, pt, ru, zh, ja, ar, hi)
- **Text Analysis**: Comprehensive analysis including:
  - Sentiment analysis (positive/negative/neutral)
  - Tone detection (formal, casual, urgent, sarcastic)
  - Bias detection (political, gender, racial)
  - Readability metrics (Flesch reading ease, grade level, etc.)
  - Emotion analysis (joy, anger, sadness, etc.)
  - Disinformation risk assessment
- **Information Synthesis**: Combine information from multiple sources into:
  - Summaries
  - Comparisons
  - Chronological timelines
  - Comprehensive reports
  - FAQs
- **Batch Processing**: Efficient processing of multiple items in a single request

#### Model Management
- Automatic model downloading from Ollama registry
- Model listing (local and remote)
- Model removal
- Model verification and integrity checking
- Disk usage monitoring
- Storage optimization features

#### API Endpoints
Added 10 new REST API endpoints under `/api/llm` prefix:
- `GET /api/llm/health` - Service health check
- `GET /api/llm/models` - List available models and status
- `GET /api/llm/capabilities` - List supported capabilities
- `POST /api/llm/generate` - Text generation
- `POST /api/llm/chat` - Chat completion
- `POST /api/llm/extract` - Text extraction
- `POST /api/llm/translate` - Translation
- `POST /api/llm/analyze` - Text analysis
- `POST /api/llm/synthesize` - Information synthesis
- `POST /api/llm/batch` - Batch processing

#### Default Models
Added support for 9 pre-configured open-source models via Ollama:
- `llama3:8b` (default) - Meta Llama 3 8B, 4.7GB
- `mistral:7b` - Mistral AI 7B, 4.1GB
- `phi3:3.8b` - Microsoft Phi-3 3.8B, 2.3GB
- `qwen2.5:7b` - Alibaba Qwen 2.5 7B, 4.8GB
- `gemma:7b` - Google Gemma 7B, 4.8GB
- `llama3:70b` - Meta Llama 3 70B, 40GB
- `llava:7b` - LLaVA 7B (multimodal), 4.5GB
- `bart-large` - Facebook BART Large, 1.4GB

### Architecture
- **Modular Design**: Clean separation of concerns with LLM service layer
- **Extensible**: Easy to add new model backends (HuggingFace, llama.cpp)
- **Portable**: Full Docker support for LLM deployment
- **Open-Source**: 100% open-source models and runtime

### Infrastructure
- `Dockerfile.llm` - Docker image with Ollama integration
- `docker-compose.llm.yml` - Docker Compose configuration for LLM
- `docker-entrypoint.sh` - Custom entrypoint for LLM services
- `requirements-llm.txt` - Python dependencies for LLM module
- `scripts/setup_llm.py` - Automated setup script

### Documentation
- Updated `README.md` with comprehensive LLM section
- Added `docs/LLM_SETUP_GUIDE.md` - Complete setup guide
- Updated `CONTRIBUTING.md` with LLM contribution guidelines
- Updated `docs/DEVELOPER_GUIDE.md` with LLM development section
- Updated `docs/USER_GUIDE.md` with LLM usage instructions
- Updated `.env.example` with LLM environment variables

### Testing
- Added `tests/test_llm.py` - Unit tests for LLM functionality
- Added `tests/test_llm_integration.py` - Integration tests
- Comprehensive test coverage for all LLM capabilities

### Configuration
- Added environment variables for LLM configuration:
  - `OLLAMA_HOST`
  - `OLLAMA_ORIGINS`
  - `DOWNLOAD_DEFAULT_MODELS`
  - `AUTO_DOWNLOAD_MODELS`
  - `MAX_CONTEXT_LENGTH`
  - `MAX_TOKENS`
  - `MODEL_LIBRARY_PATH`

### Security
- All LLM processing happens locally - no data leaves your system
- Input validation via Pydantic models
- Proper error handling and graceful degradation
- No hardcoded credentials or secrets

### Performance
- Model caching for downloaded models
- GPU acceleration (automatic when available)
- Batch processing for efficient multi-item handling
- Configurable timeouts and retries

### Breaking Changes
None - All changes are additive. Existing functionality remains unchanged.

### Migration Notes
No migration required. LLM features are opt-in and disabled by default.

### Known Issues
- Ollama must be installed and running for LLM features to work
- Large models require significant RAM and storage
- CPU-only operation is slow for models >7B parameters
- GPU acceleration requires NVIDIA GPU with CUDA support

### Dependencies
- Python 3.8+ (required for LLM support)
- Ollama (required for LLM features)
- New Python packages in `requirements-llm.txt`

---

Version 0.2.0 (2024-XX-XX)
------------------------

Initial MVP release of Open Omniscience.

### Features
- Core web scraping and crawling capabilities (HTTrack integration)
- Ethical scraping with robots.txt compliance
- Duplicate detection and filtering
- Multi-source aggregation
- Incremental updates and resume capabilities
- Unified database for scraped content
- Advanced search with Boolean operators
- Metadata extraction
- Content deduplication
- Data export in various formats
- Keyword analysis
- Link analysis
- Source management
- Category classification

### Infrastructure
- FastAPI backend
- SQLite and PostgreSQL support
- Docker support
- CI/CD pipeline
- Comprehensive logging
- Rate limiting
- Security features

